hands_on_practices.problem:
A certain topological space $M$, which is path-connected, locally path-connected, and semilocally simply-connected, is studied in a theoretical model. Its fundamental group, $\pi_1(M)$, is determined to be isomorphic to the alternating group on four elements, $A_4$. Determine the set of all possible numbers of sheets for any connected covering space of $M$.

Which one of the following options represents this complete set of possible sheet numbers?

A. {1, 2, 3, 4, 6, 12}

B. {1, 3, 4, 6, 12}

C. {1, 2, 3, 4}

D. {1, 12}

E. {3, 4, 6, 12}

F. {1, 2, 3, 4, 6}
